Class AtomAcceptedMediaRange

Represents a media range as defined in RFC 2616: Hypertext Transfer Protocol that specifies a type of representation that can be added to a AtomMemberResources.

Syntax
[Serializable]
public class AtomAcceptedMediaRange : IComparable, IExtensibleSyndicationObject, IAtomCommonObjectAttributes
Remarks

The AtomAcceptedMediaRange class implements the app:accept element of the Atom Publishing Protocol.

The content value of the MediaRange property for an AtomAcceptedMediaRange is a media range as defined in RFC 2616. The media range specifies a type of representation that can be added to a AtomMemberResources via a POST operation.

The AtomAcceptedMediaRange is similar to the HTTP Accept request-header [RFC 2616]. Media type parameters are allowed within AtomAcceptedMediaRange, but AtomAcceptedMediaRange has no notion of preference e.g. accept-params or q arguments, as specified in section 14.1 of RFC 2616 are not significant.

See http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types for a listing of the registered IANA MIME media types and sub-types.

FindExtension(Predicate<ISyndicationExtension>)

Searches for a syndication extension that matches the conditions defined by the specified predicate, and returns the first occurrence within the Extensions collection.

Declaration
public ISyndicationExtension FindExtension(Predicate<ISyndicationExtension> match)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.Predicate<ISyndicationExtension> match

The System.Predicate<T> delegate that defines the conditions of the ISyndicationExtension to search for.
Returns
Type Description
ISyndicationExtension

The first syndication extension that matches the conditions defined by the specified predicate, if found; otherwise, the default value for ISyndicationExtension.
Remarks

The System.Predicate<T> is a delegate to a method that returns true if the object passed to it matches the conditions defined in the delegate. The elements of the current Extensions are individually passed to the System.Predicate<T> delegate, moving forward in the Extensions, starting with the first element and ending with the last element. Processing is stopped when a match is found.

Exceptions
Type Condition
System.ArgumentNullException

The match is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).
